items.title: Ford turns to Amazon to give used cars sales a boost
items.description: Amazon Autos, which kicked off last year with Hyundai, initially started with new cars. The deal with Ford pushes it into used car territory.

items.title: Ramp hits $32B valuation, just 3 months after hitting $22.5B
items.description: In 2025 alone, Ramp has leapt from being worth $13 billion to $32 billion with new rounds every few months.

items.title: Cisco acquires translation startup EzDubs
items.description: Cisco has acquired Y Combinator-backed translation app EzDub to integrate it into its communication suite.

items.title: Luminar is fighting with its biggest customer as bankruptcy threat looms
items.description: The fight comes at a perilous time for Luminar, which is running out of cash and under SEC investigation.
